    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"ex10. Causal (X, no PS, SB Backend) - InvGauss/Amoroso\"\n---\n\n\n\n\n> **Website workflow note.**\n> This page reflects the current exported API and recommended wrapper-first usage.\n> Last updated: **2026-02-19**.\n>\n> For the full package narrative, see the main package vignettes (basic, unconditional, conditional, and causal).\n\n\n# Causal Inference: X Without PS (CRP+SB)\n\n## What you’ll learn\n\n- How to run the causal workflow with **outcome models conditional on X** while **disabling propensity-score estimation**.\\n- How to compare causal fits that differ in backend/tail specification while keeping the same evaluation pattern.\\n- How tail augmentation can change effect behavior in extremes even when mean effects are similar.\n\n## When to use this template\n\n- Treatment assignment is plausibly ignorable given \\(X\\), but you want to **avoid PS modeling** (or you already handled PS externally).\\n- You want causal summaries beyond the mean (quantile/conditional effects) and need flexible outcome distributions.\n\n## Key limitation (important)\n\nWith PS disabled, you rely entirely on the outcome models for adjustment. If overlap/positivity is weak, effects can be unstable; use diagnostic plots and sensitivity checks.\n\n## What this page does\n\nThis vignette uses **covariates X** but disables PS estimation. Outcome models are conditional on X only.\n\n- Model A: CRP with GPD tail (InvGauss)\n- Model B: SB bulk-only (Amoroso)\n\n---\n\n## Data Setup\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ndata(\"causal_alt_real500_p4_k2\")\ny <- abs(causal_alt_real500_p4_k2$y) + 0.01\nA <- causal_alt_real500_p4_k2$A\nX <- as.matrix(causal_alt_real500_p4_k2$X)\n\nsummary_tbl <- tibble(\n  statistic = c(\"N\", \"Mean\", \"SD\", \"Min\", \"Max\"),\n  value = c(length(y), mean(y), sd(y), min(y), max(y))\n)\n\nsummary_tbl %>%\n  mutate(value = signif(value, 4)) %>%\n  print()\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n# A tibble: 5 × 2\n  statistic    value\n  <chr>        <dbl>\n1 N         500     \n2 Mean        1.43  \n3 SD          1.08  \n4 Min         0.0126\n5 Max         8.10  \n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nx_eval <- X[1:40, , drop = FALSE]\ny_eval <- y[1:40]\nu_threshold <- as.numeric(stats::quantile(y, 0.8, names = FALSE))\n```\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Model A: CRP with GPD Tail (InvGauss)\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nparam_specs_gpd <- list(\n  gpd = list(\n    threshold = list(\n      mode = \"dist\",\n      dist = \"lognormal\",\n      args = list(meanlog = log(max(u_threshold, .Machine$double.eps)), sdlog = 0.25)\n    )\n  )\n)\n\nbundle_crp_gpd <- bundle(\n  x = y,\n  treat = A,\n  X = X,\n  kernel = \"invgauss\",\n  backend = \"crp\",\n  PS = FALSE,\n  GPD = TRUE,\n  components = 6,\n  param_specs = param_specs_gpd,\n  mcmc_outcome = list(niter = 300, nburnin = 80, nchains = 1, thin = 1, seed = 3)\n)\n\nbundle_crp_gpd\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nCausalMixGPD causal bundle\nPS model: disabled \n      Field                    Treated                    Control\n    Backend Chinese Restaurant Process Chinese Restaurant Process\n     Kernel                   invgauss                   invgauss\n Components                          6                          6\n   GPD tail                       TRUE                       TRUE\n    Epsilon                      0.025                      0.025\n\nOutcome PS included: FALSE \nn (control) = 232 | n (treated) = 268 \n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nfit_crp_gpd <- quiet_mcmc(dpmgpd.causal(bundle_crp_gpd))\nsummary(fit_crp_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n-- Outcome fits --\n[control]\nMixGPD fit | backend: Chinese Restaurant Process | kernel: Inverse Gaussian Distribution | GPD tail: TRUE\nn = 232 | components = 6 | epsilon = 0.025\nMCMC: niter=300, nburnin=80, thin=1, nchains=1 \nFit\nUse summary() for posterior summaries; plot() for diagnostics; predict() for predictions.\n\n[treated]\nMixGPD fit | backend: Chinese Restaurant Process | kernel: Inverse Gaussian Distribution | GPD tail: TRUE\nn = 268 | components = 6 | epsilon = 0.025\nMCMC: niter=300, nburnin=80, thin=1, nchains=1 \nFit\nUse summary() for posterior summaries; plot() for diagnostics; predict() for predictions.\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_mean_gpd <- predict(fit_crp_gpd, x = x_eval, type = \"mean\", interval = \"credible\", nsim_mean = 150)\nhead(pred_mean_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id    estimate        lower      upper ps\n1  1 -0.07639299  0.017586223 -0.6665044 NA\n2  2 -0.03696389 -0.044772777 -0.5911776 NA\n3  3 -0.15771371 -0.038024872 -1.5852229 NA\n4  4 -0.08543089 -0.033009185 -0.7204908 NA\n5  5 -0.05216076  0.027562015 -0.7756449 NA\n6  6 -0.04063718  0.001375115 -0.4282698 NA\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_mean_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex10-causal-x-no-ps-sb_files/figure-html/predict-mean-crp-gpd-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex10-causal-x-no-ps-sb_files/figure-html/predict-mean-crp-gpd-2.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_q_gpd <- predict(fit_crp_gpd, x = x_eval, type = \"quantile\", p = 0.5, interval = \"credible\")\nhead(pred_q_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id index  estimate      lower     upper ps\n1  1   0.5 0.1118762 -0.1212930 0.2845402 NA\n2  2   0.5 0.1149681 -0.1313326 0.3186802 NA\n3  3   0.5 0.1108223 -0.1204657 0.2930985 NA\n4  4   0.5 0.1163526 -0.1173893 0.3179941 NA\n5  5   0.5 0.1217482 -0.1079677 0.4081211 NA\n6  6   0.5 0.1085464 -0.1178059 0.2857504 NA\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_q_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex10-causal-x-no-ps-sb_files/figure-html/predict-quantile-crp-gpd-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex10-causal-x-no-ps-sb_files/figure-html/predict-quantile-crp-gpd-2.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_d_gpd <- predict(fit_crp_gpd, x = x_eval, y = y_eval, type = \"density\", interval = \"credible\")\nhead(pred_d_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id         y ps trt_estimate  trt_lower  trt_upper con_estimate  con_lower\n1  1 0.9001906 NA            1 0.42030552 0.57715508            1 0.36361256\n2  2 1.3517565 NA            2 0.29850594 0.55483542            2 0.28292338\n3  3 1.1475287 NA            3 0.35168764 0.67470167            3 0.31205392\n4  4 1.9323578 NA            4 0.21024335 0.32194340            4 0.18216727\n5  5 3.3439817 NA            5 0.03714713 0.09599312            5 0.01341044\n6  6 0.9493979 NA            6 0.41153144 0.56731353            6 0.35239327\n  con_upper\n1 0.5413887\n2 0.4881511\n3 0.5358377\n4 0.3270959\n5 0.0951366\n6 0.5400380\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_d_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex10-causal-x-no-ps-sb_files/figure-html/predict-density-crp-gpd-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_surv_gpd <- predict(fit_crp_gpd, x = x_eval, y = y_eval, type = \"survival\", interval = \"credible\")\nhead(pred_surv_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id         y ps trt_estimate  trt_lower trt_upper con_estimate   con_lower\n1  1 0.9001906 NA            1 0.61762156 0.7753665            1 0.540119571\n2  2 1.3517565 NA            2 0.41738974 0.5617026            2 0.379662588\n3  3 1.1475287 NA            3 0.50081042 0.6572798            3 0.445991161\n4  4 1.9323578 NA            4 0.22783809 0.3538417            4 0.210155212\n5  5 3.3439817 NA            5 0.03163719 0.1811628            5 0.001458124\n6  6 0.9493979 NA            6 0.59301681 0.7514624            6 0.518876811\n  con_upper\n1 0.7166897\n2 0.5316143\n3 0.6088165\n4 0.3204525\n5 0.1253399\n6 0.6919391\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_surv_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex10-causal-x-no-ps-sb_files/figure-html/predict-survival-crp-gpd-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\natt_gpd <- att(fit_crp_gpd, interval = \"credible\", nsim_mean = 150)\nhead(att_gpd)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n$fit\n[1] -0.07671231\n\n$lower\n[1] -0.7023715\n\n$upper\n[1] 0.4345992\n\n$ate\n$ate$fit\n  id    estimate      lower     upper\n1  1 -0.07671231 -0.7023715 0.4345992\n\n$ate$draws\n                [,1]\n  [1,]  0.3834179829\n  [2,]  0.4198072266\n  [3,]  0.0644123820\n  [4,]  0.1167777338\n  [5,] -0.1958546371\n  [6,] -0.1160666051\n  [7,] -0.1891614076\n  [8,] -0.1461912839\n  [9,] -0.2808836759\n [10,] -0.0929374650\n [11,] -0.4593164250\n [12,] -0.5412257550\n [13,] -0.1299953662\n [14,] -0.1095712185\n [15,] -0.3429483404\n [16,] -0.2694958156\n [17,] -0.3773807385\n [18,] -0.5343167939\n [19,] -0.2104349664\n [20,] -0.7949692736\n [21,] -0.4665551585\n [22,] -0.2307036956\n [23,] -0.2855889185\n [24,] -0.2408200173\n [25,] -0.4811744797\n [26,] -0.1990022293\n [27,] -0.2032969531\n [28,] -0.1068017450\n [29,] -0.1026571051\n [30,] -0.3709187640\n [31,] -0.5822376433\n [32,] -0.6416049333\n [33,] -0.3758331700\n [34,] -0.5010281497\n [35,] -0.6068559330\n [36,] -0.3514363650\n [37,] -0.2733128299\n [38,] -0.2296695156\n [39,] -0.2652611634\n [40,] -0.2759805667\n [41,] -0.3332178556\n [42,] -0.2683201832\n [43,] -0.3036579913\n [44,] -0.4777985793\n [45,] -0.1728157038\n [46,] -0.4068209770\n [47,] -0.4952169089\n [48,] -0.3469435010\n [49,] -0.3914550512\n [50,] -0.4314637086\n [51,] -0.5405581488\n [52,] -0.5700289698\n [53,] -0.6113326132\n [54,] -0.0783692771\n [55,] -0.0524402649\n [56,] -0.1853260903\n [57,] -0.2150212290\n [58,] -0.2278258542\n [59,] -0.3502045109\n [60,] -0.3231211693\n [61,] -0.3981782877\n [62,] -0.6811177208\n [63,] -0.6580212801\n [64,] -0.7474891630\n [65,] -0.5611382111\n [66,] -0.5254501057\n